com.efnilite.redaktor

Class RedaktorAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.efnilite.redaktor.RedaktorAPI

  • public class RedaktorAPI
extends java.lang.Object
    The main API class. The goal of this class is to make all of Redaktor's features easily usable. This class will supply the basic methods, if you don't want to dig deep in how to do specific stuff.
    See Also:
    Selection, Schematic, Pattern, Editor, com.efnilite.redaktor.event

      • getDefaultEditor

        public static Editor<org.bukkit.command.ConsoleCommandSender> getDefaultEditor()
        Get a default Editor instance. This is a way to use Editor methods in an API without using players.

        The Editor returned has an unlimited max change and does not log chances to the sender (in this case console)

        Please note that using this method can cause conflict issues with other plugins using this method, as it will return one specific Editor instance. For example: If you make a lot of changes another plugin can undo them even if you don't want to. That's why you can also just create a new instance of an Editor to avoid conflicts.

        Returns:
        The main Editor.

      • newBlockIndexGetter

        public static void newBlockIndexGetter(CuboidSelection cuboid,
                                       java.util.function.Consumer<java.util.HashMap<org.bukkit.block.Block,BlockIndex>> consumer)
        Creates a new AsyncIndexBlockGetter

        This is used for getting a lot of blocks asynchronously, including the index from position 1.

        Example: If the second block of the list of blocks is returned, the BlockIndex is 1, 0, 0. If it's the 10th block, it's 10, 0, 0.

        Parameters:
        cuboid - The cuboid.
        consumer - What to do when the blocks have been retrieved. Since this is an async thread, this is needed.
